President Obama: We understand that America's not what can be done for us, it's about what can be done by us—as one nation, as one people.""
Gov. Romney said it was 'tragic' to end the war in Iraq. I disagree. I think it was the right thing to do."—President Obama"
POTUS: We can gut education to pay for Gov. Romney’s tax cuts, or we can do what I propose—recruit 100,000 math and science teachers.""
Climate change is not a hoax. More droughts and wildfires are not a joke. They're a threat to your future."—President Obama"
President Obama: Today, the United States is less dependent on foreign oil than at any time in the last two decades.""
President Obama: I believe we can create more jobs by controlling more of our own energy.""
President Obama: A strong economy doesn’t trickle down from the top—it comes from a thriving middle class.""
President Obama: The last thing we can afford to do now is to go back to the same policies that got us into this mess in the first place.""
Manufacturing is coming back to America. Home values are back on the rise. We have come too far to turn back now."—President Obama"

We passed health care reform, also known as Obamacare, because I do care. I don’t want insurance companies jerking you around anymore.""

President Obama: I need you fired up, I need you ready to go vote. Because we've got some work to do. We've got an election to win.""
